land":"Crichton, Midlothian, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Erskine, Renfrewshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Erskine, Renfrewshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1308–":"1308–Deceased","1305–Male":"1305–Deceased","1330–1424":"1330–1424","1308–Female":"1308–Deceased","1305":"1305","1424":"1424","1330":"1330","1308":"1308","Crichton Castle, Crichton, Midlothian, Scotland":"Crichton, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom","Erskine, Renfrewshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Erskine, Renfrewshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Erskine","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from the barony of Erskine in Renfrewshire, first recorded in 1226 in the form <i>Erskyn</i>.","History: A family of this name have held a number of Scottish titles, including the earldoms of Mar, Buchan, Kellie, and Rosslyn."],"variants":[{"name":"Erskin","meanings":["Scottish (central Scotland and Fife): variant of   Erskine  . This form of the surname is now more common in the US."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Erskine was born in 1308, in Crichton, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Sir Robert Erskine. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1308–":"1308–Surnud","1305–Male":"1305–Surnud","1330–1424":"1330–1424","1308–Female":"1308–Surnud","1305":"1305","1424":"1424","1330":"1330","1308":"1308","Crichton Castle, Crichton, Midlothian, Scotland":"Crichton, Midlothian, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Erskine, Renfrewshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Erskine, Renfrewshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1308–":"1308–Kuollut","1305–Male":"1305–Kuollut","1330–1424":"1330–1424","1308–Female":"1308–Kuollut","1305":"1305","1424":"1424","1330":"1330","1308":"1308","Crichton Castle, Crichton, Midlothian, Scotland":"Crichton, Midlothian, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Erskine, Renfrewshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Erskine, Renfrewshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1308–":"1308–Décédée","1305–Male":"1305–Décédé","1330–1424":"1330–1424","1308–Female":"1308–Décédée","1305":"1305","1424":"1424","1330":"1330","1308":"1308","Crichton Castle, Crichton, Midlothian, Scotland":"Crichton, Midlothian, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Erskine, Renfrewshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Erskine, Renfrewshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Erskine est née en 1308, à Crichton, Midlothian, Écosse, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Sir Robert Erskine. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1308–":"1308–Verstorben","1305–Male":"1305–Verstorben","1330–1424":"1330–1424","1308–Female":"1308–Verstorben","1305":"1305","1424":"1424","1330":"1330","1308":"1308","Crichton Castle, Crichton, Midlothian, Scotland":"Crichton, Midlothian, Schottland, United Kingdom","Erskine, Renfrewshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Erskine, Renfrewshire, Schottland, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Erskine wurde 1308 in